The Studio@620 hosts a conversation between St. Petersburg authors Peter Kageyama (”Hunters Point”) and Paul Wilborn (”Florida Hustle”) about their novels, hosted by studio co-founder Bob Devin Jones, at 8 p.m. Feb. 7 at the studio, 620 First Ave. S, St. Petersburg. Doors open at 7:30. Free, with books available for sale and signing. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.